messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Hey, can you get an ambulance and a cop over to 59 Alderwood Drive?
59 what?
Alderwood. A-L-D-E-R-W-O-O-D. She just attacked me with a knife, and I had to shoot her.
Okay, I have help on the way. You said 59 Alderwood Street?
Alderwood, A-L-D-E-R-W-O-O-D.
Okay, stay on the line with me. Is she breathing?
I don't know. Hang on a second.
Are you okay?
Alderwood, A-L-D-E-R-W-O-O-D, hurry.
Okay, I have it. Adam, Lincoln, David?
Delta, Delta, E-R, Wood.
Are you in Los Angeles County?
No, no, Stafford, Virginia.
This is for Las Cruces, New Mexico. Are you located in Las Cruces, New Mexico?
I'm in Virginia. I'm in Virginia.
You're in Virginia?
Yes.
I need you to stay on the line with me.
I'm calling 911 on my cell phone as well. Give me one moment.
Okay, I have help on the way. Give me one second.
Thank you.
Can you confirm your address is 59 Alderwood Drive? Your wife attacked you with a knife and you had to shoot her?
Alderwood, A-L-D-E-R-W-O-O-D.
Okay. Stay on the line with me.
A-L-D-E-R, A-Alpha, L-Lincoln, D-Delta, E-R, Wood.
I have help on the way. Alderwood, A-L-D-E-R-W-O-O-D.
Okay, sir, can you hear me?
Yes, it's on my holster.
Sir, can you hear me?
I'm an FBI agent.
Please, stay on the line with me.
Yes, ma'am.
Are you able to put the weapon down safely?
Yes, I'll put it right on the counter, okay? There's a dog, but she's not.
Sir, can you hear me?
Yes, it's on the counter.
Sir, can you hear me?
Yeah.
What do you mean?
Please, hurry.
Yes, yes, yes. Help is on the way.
She cut me on the arm.
Is she breathing?
I think so, but I don't know. It doesn't look like she is.
